<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871229-0083 </DOCNO><HL> Macmillan Unit Buys Clymer</HL><DD> 12/29/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MLLTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Macmillan Inc. said a unit, Intertec Publishing Corp., has acquired Burbank, Calif.-based Clymer Publications, a closely held publisher of automotive repair and service manuals. Terms weren't disclosed.    &quot;The acquisition of Clymer will position Intertec as the premier publisher of mechanical 'how to' manuals,&quot; said Edward P. Evans, chairman and chief executive officer of Macmillan. </TEXT></DOC>